# Trivy IaC misconfiguration suppressions for code-guru.
#
# Format: one Trivy AVD/check ID per line. Comments document WHY a finding
# is suppressed so the next reader does not re-litigate the decision.

# AVD-DS-0026 / DS-0026 — "No HEALTHCHECK defined" (LOW)
#
# The image is built FROM gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot, which
# ships no shell, no curl, no wget, and no busybox. A Dockerfile HEALTHCHECK
# directive that shells out cannot be expressed against this base image.
#
# In production, code-guru runs on AKS (see ExampleOrg/shared-toolbox
# stacks/03_code_guru) where a kubelet livenessProbe + readinessProbe hit
# /health directly. The Dockerfile-level HEALTHCHECK is therefore both
# unimplementable and redundant for the only deployment target we support.
AVD-DS-0026
